comments: Vanderbilt (UTA) brings his hands forward prior to marginal contact occurring with Poole's (GSW) side as they each attempt to establish rebounding position.
Conley (UTA) is already in Jerome's (GSW) path and is turning away from Jerome before marginal contact occurs as they come together during the loose ball.
Jerome (GSW) extends laterally and initiates contact with Markkanen's (UTA) front and side during the drive.
Vanderbilt (UTA) brings his arms forward slightly prior to marginal contact occurring with Poole's (GSW) side as the screen is set.
Poole (GSW) engages and disengages with Markkanen (UTA) as Markkanen moves to set the pick.
Lamb (GSW) and Markkanen (UTA) engage and disengage with one another as the pick expires.
Jerome (GSW) contests the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Clarkson's (UTA) arm after the release.

Conley (UTA) brushes Poole's (GSW) right arm and marginal contact occurs as Poole elevates for the driving shot attempt. Olynyk (UTA) jumps vertically alongside Poole's path and legally contests the driving shot attempt.
Poole (GSW) brings his off-arm outward as he elevates and marginal contact occurs with Olynyk (UTA) as Olynyk defends the driving shot attempt.
Lamb (GSW) maintains a rested hand on Conley's (UTA) left hip and releases away without applying any force as Conley elevates for the floater attempt.
Olynyk (UTA) brings his left arm toward Jerome's (GSW) upper body and marginal contact occurs as Olynyk elevates for the rebound.
Olynyk (UTA) and Lamb (GSW) make incidental body contact with one another during rebounding.
Lamb (GSW) legally contests Olynyk's (UTA) shot attempt, which Green (GSW) cleanly blocks.
Poole (GSW) dribbles the ball off of Clarkson's (UTA) planted right leg and Clarkson does not intentionally kick the ball.
Clarkson (UTA) brings his arm down toward Poole's (GSW) upper body and marginal contact occurs prior to the timeout being recognized.
Clarkson (UTA) brings his left forearm toward DiVincenzo's (GSW) path and marginal contact occurs with DiVincenzo's front as he drives toward the lane.
Olynyk (UTA) and Jerome (GSW) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.
Jerome (GSW) initiates contact with Olynyk's (UTA) right arm after Olynyk re-gains control of the ball and is attempting the shot near the rim.
Lamb (GSW) and Markkanen (UTA) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
Clarkson (UTA) and DiVincenzo (GSW) engage and disengage with one another as they move beyond the perimeter.
DiVincenzo (GSW) and Olynyk (UTA) come together at the same spot and incidental body contact occurs after Olynyk retrieves the loose ball.
Green (GSW) initiates body contact with Clarkson's (UTA) left side after he receives the pass.
Green (GSW) and Vanderbilt (UTA) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.

Olynyk (UTA) and Lamb (GSW) engage under the rim. Both players play aggressively for position, until the contact becomes too physical, with no definitive committer.  A double foul is the most appropriate call on this play with the ball retained by GSW as they had imminent possession at the time of the foul.
Olynyk (UTA) continues to move forward and does not establish a legal guarding position prior to body contact occurring with Poole (GSW).
Conley (UTA) commits a take foul on DiVincenzo (GSW). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
DiVincenzo (GSW) legally contests Markkanen's (UTA) jump shot attempt.
Poole (GSW) maintains a rested forearm on Olynyk's (UTA) body and marginal contact occurs as Olynyk's momentum continues to carry him forward under the basket during the long rebound.
Conley (UTA) rests his hands on Lamb's (GSW) back and releases away without applying any force as the ball falls toward them during rebounding.
Clarkson (UTA) commits a take foul on Poole (GSW).
Lamb (GSW) and DiVincenzo (GSW) legally contest Conley's (UTA) jump shot attempt.
